Because of high interest rates, there are fewer buyers are in the market. Those who are looking to purchase can often negotiate more effectively.
Whether it’s covering closing costs or a simple price reduction, sellers might be more willing to honor these requests.

You’d griddy too. Celebration at the end 😂

They did it! First home purchase is checked off the list. Big congratulations to Lauren and Johnny for accomplishing this huge milestone. The goal was to capitalize on the current market and find a deal that likely wouldn’t be here once interest rates drop. 

After weeks of searching and listening to me talk about finding value 😂, they finally found the perfect fit in the 33rd best community in the nation according to RCLCO.

Location matters. Properties in prime locations hold their value better, even in a down market. When the market rebounds, these properties are likely to gain value faster.

Congratulations to my clients! This deal was a journey 😂. Before they got under contract with this home, they went through a roller coaster of emotions. Initially, we backed out of another home under contract due to issues the inspector uncovered during the option period. Then, unfortunately, we lost a bidding war for another property to a buyer who not only offered significantly above list price, but also waived appraisal contingencies (it was like the 2020 real estate market all over again). With all of that behind us, this home popped up and exceeded all expectations. After successfully navigating the option period, we’re on the way to closing. 🤞🏿
